data.text:
Canberra, Australia

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: -35.282001, 149.128998.

Canberra is the capital city of Australia, its business, commercial, financial, and administrative center. It is located in the area known as the Australian Capital Territory. It is one of the largest cities in the country and is a tourist attraction, with plenty of points of interest and things to do. Canberra is a planned community and a large modern city. It is situated in the southeastern part of the country, and it was proclaimed the capital city in the early 19th century. Today it is a modern community and a home to the country's Parliament House and most of the administrative bodies.

Geographically, the city enjoys a wonderful location, in a large valley surrounded by picturesque hills and the climatic conditions of the area are wonderful, with soft cool summers and hot but dry winters. Local landmarks and attractions in and around the city include Canberra Museum & Gallery, National Portrait Gallery, Nishi Gallery, Drill Hall Gallery, Civic Square, Old Parliament House, Questacon - National Science and Technology Centre, National Carillon, Blundells Cottage, Commonwealth Park, Canberra Nara Peace Park, National Library of Australia, Royal Australian Mint, Australian National Botanic Gardens, and Australian War Memorial.
